message.content: A 'Symphyotrichum divaricatum' is a species of flowering plant in the Asteraceae family. It is commonly known as a 'White wood aster', and is native to eastern and central North America. The plant typically grows between 1 and 3 feet tall with a spread of 1 to 2 feet. Its flowers are small and white, with yellow centers, and are arranged in compact clusters. The leaves of the plant are alternate and have a toothed margin. 'Symphyotrichum divaricatum' prefers moist, well-drained soil and can be found in woodland borders, shady meadows, and along roadsides. Its visual characteristics include a bushy shape, white daisy-like flowers, and green leaves with sharply toothed margins.
